HEADWORD: Posthouse
<hw>Post"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
house established for the convenience of the post, where relays of
horses can be obtained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A house for distributing the malls; a post
office.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Posthumed</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Posthume</ent>⟦br⟧
